<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1739,2091]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,1739,1765]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">Habitat:—</emphasis>
This species was found on a limestone cliff in a shallow cave in deep shade beneath scrubby karst vegetation. It was growing in thin dusty soil on a slightly damp mossy rock.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="69" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1739,2091]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,356,1812,1838]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">Etymology:—</emphasis>
The epithet refers to the name of Sangkulirang, the Limestone Karst Mountain Ecosystem where this species was found.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1451,1739,2091]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,617,1883,1909]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68">Provisional Conservation Status:—</emphasis>
Vulnerable (VU, D2). This species is only known from single collection from the Sangkulirang Mangkalihat Limestone Karst Ecosystem. The area does not yet have legal protected status, and there are clear signs of anthropogenic disturbance (oil palm plantations and mining) around the karst formations. As a karst micro-endemic it therefore is ‘prone to the effects of human activities or stochastic events within a very short time period in an uncertain future’ (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Subcommittee" box="[532,1108,2028,2054]" pageId="6" pageNumber="68" refId="ref6233" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee." type="book" year="2019">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee 2019</bibRefCitation>
). An ex-situ initiative has been started with plants being cultivated at Kebun Raya Bogor (Bogor Botanic Garden).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,158,364]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,158,184]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Notes:</emphasis>
—There are four other caulescent species in 
<emphasis box="[780,797,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B</emphasis>
. sect. 
<emphasis box="[873,1018,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Petermannia</emphasis>
in Borneo with conspicuously peltate leaves: 
<taxonomicName authority="Sands (1990: 81)" authorityName="Sands" authorityPageNumber="81" authorityYear="1990" box="[222,578,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amphioxus">
<emphasis box="[222,375,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. amphioxus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sands, M. J. S." box="[383,578,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="57 - 85" refId="ref6823" refString="Sands, M. J. S. (1990) Six new Begonias from Sabah. Kew Magazine 7: 57 - 85." type="journal article" year="1990">Sands (1990: 81)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Merrill (1928: 529)" authorityName="Merrill" authorityPageNumber="529" authorityYear="1928" box="[591,979,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baramensis">
<emphasis box="[591,752,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. baramensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Merrill, E. D." box="[760,979,194,221]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="513 - 557" refId="ref6590" refString="Merrill, E. D. (1928) A collection of plants from Sarawak. Sarawak Museum Journal 3: 513 - 557." type="journal article" year="1928">Merrill (1928: 529)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Kiew (2001 b: 272)" authorityName="Kiew" authorityPageNumber="272" authorityYear="2001" box="[987,1403,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="layang-layang">
<emphasis box="[987,1181,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. layang-layang</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kiew, R." box="[1188,1403,194,220]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="241 - 268" refId="ref6414" refString="Kiew, R. (2001 b) The limestone Begonias of Sabah, Borneo - flagship species for conservation. Gardens' Bulletin Singapore 53: 241 - 268." type="journal article" year="2001">Kiew (2001b: 272)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Joffre (2015: 35)" authorityName="Joffre" authorityPageNumber="35" authorityYear="2015" box="[136,569,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nothobaramensis">
<emphasis box="[136,363,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. nothobaramensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Joffre, A. A. &amp; Kiew, R. &amp; Julia, S. &amp; Repin, R." box="[372,569,230,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" pagination="7 - 50" refId="ref6263" refString="Joffre, A. A., Kiew, R., Julia, S. &amp; Repin, R. (2015) The Begoniaceae of Brunei Darussalam, Borneo, including two new species. Sandakania 20: 7 - 50." type="journal article" year="2015">Joffre (2015: 35)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ardi, Girm. &amp; Randi. A. Habit" authorityYear="2022" box="[583,890,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sangkulirangensis">
<emphasis box="[583,890,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Begonia sangkulirangensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
