<taxonomicName authorityName="Joffre" authorityYear="2015" box="[1044,1271,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nothobaramensis">
<emphasis box="[1044,1271,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. nothobaramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as discussed in the diagnosis above, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merrill" authorityYear="1928" box="[425,587,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="baramensis">
<emphasis box="[425,587,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. baramensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a much larger plant, reaching up to 
<quantity box="[1034,1079,266,292]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
tall (
<bibRefCitation author="Kiew, R. &amp; Sang, J. &amp; Repin, R. &amp; Ahmad, J. A." box="[1139,1338,266,293]" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" refId="ref6486" refString="Kiew, R., Sang, J., Repin, R. &amp; Ahmad, J. A. (2015) A Guide to Begonias of Borneo. Natural History Publications (Borneo), Kota Kinabalu. 293 pp." type="book" year="2015">
Kiew 
<emphasis box="[1210,1268,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sands" authorityYear="1990" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amphioxus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">Begonia amphioxus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kiew" authorityYear="2001" box="[310,502,302,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="7" pageNumber="69" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="layang-layang">
<emphasis box="[310,502,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="69">B. layang-layang</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
do not appear to be closely allied, both differing most obviously in their leaves which are acute at the base and tip.
</paragraph>
